This paper focuses on developing a spatiotemporal model for video classification using deep learning techniques such as CNNs and RNNs. The paper specifically mentions object detection and localization, which are common topics in computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the use of attention modules in the CNN stage is a popular technique in deep learning research (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of deep learning for classification (cs.AI) and the Moving MNIST dataset, which is a common benchmark dataset for video classification (cs.MM). Finally, the paper uses deep learning models to handle sequential data, which is a common topic in neural networks research (cs.NE).
